comment:
* Data class used to represent the initial configuration of a group of safety sources.
 *
 * @hide

variables.name: SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_COLLAPSIBLE
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the safety sources group should be displayed as a collapsible group with an
     * icon (stateless or stateful) and an optional default summary.
     *
     * @deprecated use {@link #SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_STATEFUL} instead.

variables.name: SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_STATEFUL
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the safety sources group should be displayed as a group that may contribute to
     * the overall Safety Center status. This is indicated by a group stateful icon. If all sources
     * in the group have an unspecified status then a stateless group icon might be applied.

variables.name: SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_RIGID
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the safety sources group should be displayed as a rigid group with no icon and
     * no summary.
     *
     * @deprecated use {@link #SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_STATELESS} instead.

variables.name: SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_STATELESS
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the safety sources group should be displayed as a group that does not
     * contribute to the overall Safety Center status. All sources of type dynamic in the group can
     * only report an unspecified status. The stateless icon and summary may be ignored and not be
     * displayed.

variables.name: SAFETY_SOURCES_GROUP_TYPE_HIDDEN
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the safety sources group should not be displayed. All sources in the group
     * must be of type issue-only.

variables.name: STATELESS_ICON_TYPE_NONE
variables.comment:
* Indicates that no special icon will be displayed by a safety sources group when all the
     * sources contained in it are stateless.

variables.name: STATELESS_ICON_TYPE_PRIVACY
variables.comment:
* Indicates that the privacy icon will be displayed by a safety sources group when all the
     * sources contained in it are stateless.

methods.name: public int getType()
methods.comment: Returns the type of this safety sources group.

methods.name: public String getId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the id of this safety sources group. * *

The id is unique among safety sources groups in a Safety Center configuration.

methods.name: public int getTitleResId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the resource id of the title of this safety sources group. * *

The id refers to a string resource that is either accessible from any resource context or * that is accessible from the same resource context that was used to load the Safety Center * configuration. The id is {@link Resources#ID_NULL} when a title is not provided.

methods.name: public int getSummaryResId()
methods.comment:
* Returns the resource id of the summary of this safety sources group. * *

The id refers to a string resource that is either accessible from any resource context or * that is accessible from the same resource context that was used to load the Safety Center * configuration. The id is {@link Resources#ID_NULL} when a summary is not provided.

methods.name: public int getStatelessIconType()
methods.comment:
* Returns the stateless icon type of this safety sources group. * *

If set to a value other than {@link SafetySourcesGroup#STATELESS_ICON_TYPE_NONE}, the icon * specified will be displayed for collapsible groups when all the sources contained in the * group are stateless.

methods.name: public List<SafetySource> getSafetySources()
methods.comment:
* Returns the list of {@link SafetySource}s in this safety sources group. * *

A safety sources group contains at least one {@link SafetySource}.

methods.name: public void writeToParcel(@NonNull Parcel dest, int flags)
